        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>JADE Application Guidelines</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3">The JADe platform aims to empower debaters, public speakers, and adjudicators by providing resources, community support, and professional growth opportunities. To maintain a constructive and high-quality environment, please review and follow the application guidelines below.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>1. Eligibility and Role Requirements</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>General Users (Debaters, Public Speakers, Adjudicators):</strong> No specific prior experience is required; however, applicants should have a genuine interest in debate, public speaking, or adjudication.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Subject Specialists:</strong> Specialists must have documented expertise or certification in a relevant subject. Specializations in public speaking, debate techniques, or adjudication standards are preferred.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>User Support Agents:</strong> Prior experience in customer support or user assistance is ideal. Agents are expected to understand JADe’s policies and user conduct guidelines.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>2. Application Process for Each Role</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Step 1: Complete Online Application</strong><br /> Fill out the application form on the JADe website and select the appropriate user role. Incomplete applications may be delayed.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Step 2: Submit Documentation</strong><br /> Subject Specialists must provide credentials, while User Support Agents should submit a resume detailing support experience.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Step 3: Review of Conduct Guidelines</strong><br /> All users must review and accept JADe’s policies regarding respectful interaction, privacy, and feedback submission.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>3. Guidelines for Platform Use and Conduct</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Resource Access and Management:</strong> Users are encouraged to actively utilize JADe resources. Subject Specialists should adhere to the quality standards set by JADe.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Interactions with Subject Specialists and User Support Agents:</strong> Users can contact specialists for guidance and are encouraged to reach out to user support agents for assistance.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Feedback and Review:</strong> Users can provide feedback on resources and interactions. Feedback should be constructive and respectful.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>4. Technical Requirements and Access</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Internet Access:</strong> An internet connection is required to register, log in, and interact with platform resources.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Browser Compatibility:</strong> The JADe application is compatible with modern web browsers. Ensure your browser is updated to avoid technical issues.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>5. Privacy and Data Security</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3">JADe is committed to protecting user data. All users must respect privacy policies and refrain from sharing sensitive information outside the platform. Unauthorized access or misuse may lead to account suspension.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>6. Application Review and Acceptance</strong></p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Processing Time:</strong> Application processing may take up to two weeks. Approved applicants will receive instructions on account setup.</p>
        <p class="p-line-height3"><strong>Appeal Process:</strong> If your application is declined, you may reach out to support@jade.org for further clarification.</p>

